org.dockbox.selene.integrated.sql

Class SQLMan<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dockbox.selene.integrated.sql.SQLMan<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the target source of a implementation. This is typically passed into getConnection(Object) and getContext(Object) dynamically, so implementations can act on the given source. If a source should be constant, the implementation should make this type Void.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    InjectableType, ISQLMan<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SQLiteMan

    public abstract class SQLMan<T>
extends Object
implements ISQLMan<T>
    Mid-level manager for communicating with SQL instances. Acts as middlewhere between DSL and Table. All functionality inside this manager is designed to expose only the methods as defined in ISQLMan.
